# Testing Rules

- Write tests around behavior and contracts, not implementation details.
- Prefer deterministic tests; avoid time/network randomness without controlled mocks.
- Keep test setup minimal and close to the subject under test.
- Cover success path, validation errors, and permission/error boundaries.
- For UI tests, assert accessible roles/text and user-visible outcomes.
- Keep integration tests for cross-module flows and unit tests for pure logic.
